description.narrative: With a gross enrolment rate of 91.2%, and a pupil-teacher ratio of 56, educational provision in Chad remains insufficient. Accommodation capacities in terms of pedagogical supervision and infrastructure require significant support. This explains why in 2021, UNICEF contributed to improving access and quality through the construction of classrooms (while ensuring that constructions are disability and gender-sensitive), the distribution of school materials and the hiring of teachers. In addition, 185,060 students (77,796 girls) were supported by 2,269 contract teachers (363 women) paid by UNICEF, in five provinces (Kanem, Lac, Logone Oriental, Mandoul and Sila). | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:23/01/2022
